description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shropshire Community Health NHS Trust an exciting opportunity for a Band 5 community staff nurse to join the South West Neighbourhood Team (ICS/IDT) for 28.5 hours per week.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be supported to undertake a wide range of clinical skills, for planned, urgent and admission avoidance care. The post holder must be willing to embark on further training as required and to work closely with other members of the multidisciplinary team within the wider health and social care economy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service operates between the hours of 8am -8pm and is a seven day, 365 days a year service. The community staff nurse role does involve working regular weekends and some Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this is a community post, the successful candidate will need to be able to meet the travel requirements of the posts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a fresh challenge, like caring for patients in their own home and feel you have the skills we are looking for, we’d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits to the team welcomed during the application process.&lt;/p&gt;
